original: Bordin, Gustav Torsten Natanael, komminister, Stjärnorp, f. 18/11/06 i Vist, östergötl. 1., av banmäst. Gustaf B. o. Hulda Johansson. G. 37 m. Greta Petersson. Barn: Anders f. 38, Birgitta 40, Lennart 43. — Stud:ex. i Linköp. 26, teol. fil. ex. 28, teol. kand. 31, prakt. teol. prov samt prästv. f. Linköp. stift 32. Past:adj. o. v. pastor i Bkeby 32, kyrkoadj. i Ledberg 36, kommin. i Stjärnorp 37.
translated: Bordin, Gustav Torsten Natanael, vicar, Stjärnorp, born on 18/11/06 in Vist, östergötl. 1., son of railway master Gustaf B. and Hulda Johansson. Married in 1937 to Greta Petersson. Children: Anders b. 1938, Birgitta b. 1940, Lennart b. 1943. He completed his high school education in Linköping in 1926, received a degree in theology in 1928, completed practical training in theology and ordained in the Linköping diocese in 1932. He served as a curate and assistant pastor in Bkeby in 1932 and a church assistant in Ledberg in 1936 before becoming a vicar in Stjärnorp in 1937.
